If you’re looking to score Alabama Crimson Tide football tickets, GoTickets is your go-to destination. Our wide selection and easy-to-use interface make it easy for you to experience all the action in person!

University of Alabama Football: A Tradition of Excellence

When it comes to college football, few teams can match the rich history and astounding success of the Crimson Tide. Well known for impressive gameplay, passionate fans, and heated rivalries, this storied squad has cemented its reputation as a force to be reckoned with. 

In fact, the famous UA football club earned its current moniker during its 1907 Iron Bowl against the Auburn University Tigers. As both teams battled it out on the messy field, the iron-rich soil covered the crisp white uniforms of the Alabama players in deep red mud. A local sports editor could only describe the scene as a “Crimson Tide,” and the new nickname stuck.

Since then, fans have watched this team play in numerous post-season bowl games and win an inconceivable number of conference championships. The tradition of excellence continues, and now you can be a part of the excitement. Don't miss your chance to see the incomparable University of Alabama team take on the competition. Buy Crimson Tide football tickets today!

Alabama Crimson Tide Football Schedule

The first step in planning your game-day adventure is to check out this year’s Alabama Crimson Tide Football schedule. Whether you're a die-hard fan or just looking to witness a rousing rivalry, there's bound to be a perfect game for you.

High-stakes Southeastern Conference matchups are always a popular choice. Take your place in the stands as the Tide competes against long-standing adversaries like the LSU Tigers, Ole Miss Rebels, or the Tennessee Volunteers. SEC powerhouses never fail to deliver, and you might even catch a season-ending touchdown or a future NFL great’s most pivotal college play.

Stadium seats sell out quickly, so there’s no time to waste. Grab your tickets, mark your calendar, and get ready for some fantastic football!

Bryant-Denny Stadium Information & Parking

If you’re headed to a home game, you’ll have the privilege of visiting Bryant-Denny Stadium. This enormous facility can accommodate over 100,000 fans and is one of the most common destinations in the Heart of Dixie. Originally named after former UA President, George H. Denny, the stadium now honors longtime Crimson Tide coach, Paul “Bear” Bryant, who led his team to six NCAA championships.

Alabama Crimson Tide Football games draw large crowds, and spots close to the stadium typically fill up fast. Be sure to consider your transportation and parking options ahead of time. Book a parking place in advance, or explore alternative transportation options like public transit or ridesharing services. Whatever you choose, arrive early so you can focus on getting straight to the field.

Game Day Activities & Tailgating Traditions

Game day isn’t only about what happens on the field—it's an all-day event. Before kickoff, take some time to check out the various activities going on around the venue. Check out the Walk of Champions, or dance to the beats of the Million Dollar Band. From open parties to live music performances, there's something for everyone.

One of the most beloved traditions in sports is tailgating, and University of Alabama football fans do it big! Join in the festivities or plan a pre-game celebration of your own. Grill up some delicious food, play games, and enjoy the camaraderie of the Crimson Tide community. The welcoming atmosphere will make you feel like part of the team.

Roll Tide!

Alabama is always full of surprises, so what are you waiting for? Get your Alabama Crimson Tide Football tickets, gear up, and prepare for an unforgettable day of college football fun. 

FAQ

Who is the University of Alabama's biggest football rival?

UA football fans have enjoyed storied rivalries for over a century, but the annual Iron Bowl against Auburn University is the apex of cross-state competition. Crimson Tide football tickets sell fast, so grab them while you can!

Where is the student section at Bryant-Denny Stadium?

UA student seating is available in sections SS2-SS5, S1-S8, and AA-EE. Fans with Alabama Crimson Tide football tickets in these areas can generally expect more exuberant and vocal crowds around them.

What is the Ivory Club?

The Bryant-Denny Stadium Ivory Club offers fans an opportunity to watch Alabama Crimson Tide football games in air-conditioned club rooms that include premium amenities and hospitality options.

Do Alabama football games sell out quickly?

University of Alabama Crimson Tide football tickets often sell out before the team officially takes the field. If you act fast, GoTickets can help you find available seats at sold-out games each season.

Do I need a parking pass for Crimson Tide games?

Parking passes are highly recommended, especially for the most popular matchups. Check GoTickets for University of Alabama Crimson Tide football tickets and parking passes.
